		<div class="comment-body"><p>Great show Jack But I disagree about solar PV costing a premium over grid power. Like most things, it depends. In my case, the lower cost of buying off-grid property more than made up the cost for installing solar PV. By purchasing land without access to grid power, I was able to get a year-round creek and pond. In addition, solar PV can be purchased and installed incrementally over time without creating more debt.</p>
