		<div class="comment-author vcard">
			<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/379e3ab6cc99a0a2a26be5cc2a3ef087?s=48&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />
			<cite class="fn">Lidia Seebeck</cite>

			<span class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
				|
				<a href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/931-common-questions/comment-page-1#comment-180947">
				June 29, 2012 at 4:50 pm</a>
					|
													</span><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->
		</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
		
		<div class="comment-body"><p>Total agreement about the hotels. As you know I live in El Paso County, Colorado. We&#8217;re still dealing with the Waldo Canyon Fire. The night the fireball hit Mountain Shadows (Tuesday), almost every hotel room in Colorado Springs&#8211; and all but 150 in Pueblo&#8211; were quickly booked. People really didn&#8217;t want to be in the shelters&#8211; plenty of space  there. Campsites  were quickly booked as well. Remember that we had some 30,000 people  needing a room in one single  evening (there are so, so many lessons coming out of this fire. Lots to tell.) By the way, before anyone asks,  I&#8217;m way at the south end of the county. An idiot trucker nearly wrecking one of our freeway exits has been more trouble for us than this fire has been. We are safe.</p>
</div>

	</div><!-- #comment-##  -->

	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		</ol>

		
	
			
